dct_title_s: Cambridgshire : described with the deuision of the hundreds, the townes situation, with the armes of the colleges of that famous vniuersiti : and also the armes of all such princes and noble-men as have heretofore borne the honorable tytles & dignities of the earldome of Cambridg
dct_description_sm: Relief shown pictorially. Bordered by the arms of the colleges and peers. Facsimile. Original imprint: "And are to be solde in popes head alley, by John Sudbury and G. Humbell. Anno 1610." Inset: Cambridge. Royal arms in upper right above title.
